properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 9 at 3:39AM PST until February 10 at 3:00AM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Areas of northeast winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to
45 mph expected.

* WHERE...Ventura County Coast.

* WHEN...From 3 PM this afternoon to 3 AM PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and
make driving difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Roadways affected by strong cross winds
include Highway 101 and Pacific Coast Highway.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 3 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 3 AM PST MONDAY
